<subSubSection id="358E8881A33765575ACAFF5B6F9E5827" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA33765575ACAFF5B6F9E5827" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33765575ACAFF5B6D2959C3" bold="true" box="[199,295,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Biology.</emphasis>
The larva was observed feeding on 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A337655758B5FF5B6FBD59C3" box="[696,947,222,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dichrostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A337655758B5FF5B6FBD59C3" box="[696,947,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">Dichrostachys cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A337655759CDFF5B682259C2" box="[960,1068,222,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) in late February. Adult emerged 7.iii (
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA33765575ADFFE876DC35826" author="Staude, H. S. &amp; Maclean, M. &amp; Mecenero, S. &amp; Pretorius, R. J. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. &amp; Van Noort, S. &amp; Sharp, A. &amp; Sharp, I. &amp; Balona, J. &amp; Bradley, S. &amp; Brink, M. &amp; Morton, A. S. &amp; Botha, M. J. &amp; Collins, S. C. &amp; Grobler, Q. &amp; Edge, D. A. &amp; Williams, M. C. &amp; Sihvonen, P." box="[210,461,258,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" pagination="1 - 380" refId="ref16473" refString="Staude, H. S., Maclean, M., Mecenero, S., Pretorius, R. J., Oberprieler, R. G., Van Noort, S., Sharp, A., Sharp, I., Balona, J., Bradley, S., Brink, M., Morton, A. S., Botha, M. J., Collins, S. C., Grobler, Q., Edge, D. A., Williams, M. C. &amp; Sihvonen, P. (2020) An overview of Lepidoptera-host-parasitoid associations for southern Africa, including an illustrated report on 2 370 African Lepidoptera-host and 119 parasitoid-Lepidoptera associations. Metamorphosis, 31 (3), 1 - 380." type="journal article" year="2020">
Staude 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33765575B2AFE866D565827" box="[295,344,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">et al</emphasis>
. 2020: 55
</bibRefCitation>
). First host-plant record for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
